Let $\theta = \angle BCP$ and $\phi = \angle CDP.$ We have $\theta + \phi = 180^\circ - \angle BCD = 90^\circ.$ By the Law of Cosines on $\triangle BCP$ and $\triangle CDP,$ we have
\begin{align*}
\cos \theta &= \frac{r_1^2 + 25/4 - 4r_1}{5r_1}, \\
\cos \phi &= \frac{r_2^2 + 25/4 - 4r_2}{5r_2}.
\end{align*}Then $\sin \theta = \sqrt{1 - \cos^2 \theta}$ and $\sin \phi = \sqrt{1 - \cos^2 \phi}.$ It follows that
\begin{align*}
r_1 &= \frac{5r_1 \sin \theta}{1 + \sin \theta} = \frac{25}{9 - 5 \cos \theta}, \\
r_2 &= \frac{5r_2 \sin \phi}{1 + \sin \phi} = \frac{5}{2 - 2 \cos \phi}.
\end{align*}Therefore,
\begin{align*}
r_1 + r_2 &= \frac{25}{9 - 5 \cos \theta} + \frac{5}{2 - 2 \cos \phi} \\
&= \frac{25(2 - 2 \cos \phi) + 5(9 - 5 \cos \theta)}{(9 - 5 \cos \theta)(2 - 2 \cos \phi)} \\
&= \frac{45 - 25 \cos \theta - 10 \cos \phi + 10 \cos \theta \cos \phi}{18 - 10 \cos \theta - 10 \cos \phi + 5 \cos \theta \cos \phi} \\
&= \frac{45 - 25 \cos \theta - 10 \cos \phi + 10 \cos \theta \cos \phi}{22 - 10 \cos \theta - 10 \cos \phi}.
\end{align*}We have $\cos \theta = \frac{BC}{BP} = \frac{5/2}{r_1 + 3},$ and similarly, $\cos \phi = \frac{5/2}{r_2 + 2}.$ Substituting these into the above expression, we get
\[r_1 + r_2 = \frac{25}{4} - \frac{15}{2} \cdot \frac{r_1 + r_2}{r_1 + 3} - 5 \cdot \frac{r_1 + r_2}{r_2 + 2} + 15 \cdot \frac{r_1 + r_2}{(r_1 + 3)(r_2 + 2)}.\]Solving for $r_1 + r_2,$ we find $r_1 + r_2 = \frac{25}{4} - \frac{45}{4} + \frac{15}{2} + \frac{15}{2} = \frac{25}{2}.$ Therefore, $k + m + n + p = 2 + 25 + 2 + 4 = \boxed{33}.$

Let $O_1$ and $O_2$ be the centers of the circles with radius 3 at $A$ and $B,$ respectively, and let $O_3$ and $O_4$ be the centers of the circles with radius 2 at $C$ and $D,$ respectively. Let $O$ be the center of the circle tangent to all four circles.

