Let $N$ be the foot of the altitude from $K$ to $JL.$  Then $\angle KNL = 90^\circ,$ so by the Law of Sines on triangle $KNL,$
\[\frac{NL}{\sin 60^\circ} = \frac{KL}{\sin 30^\circ}.\]Since $KL = 2NL,$
\[NL = \frac{\sqrt{3}}{3} KL = \frac{2 \sqrt{3}}{3}.\]Then $JN = JL - NL = 1 - \frac{2 \sqrt{3}}{3} = \frac{1}{3} (3 - 2 \sqrt{3}).$

Let $P$ be the foot of the altitude from $M$ to $JL,$ and let $Q$ be the foot of the altitude from $M$ to $JK.$

