Then $JP = JN + NP = \frac{1}{3} (3 - 2 \sqrt{3}) + x \cos 75^\circ$ and $KQ = KN - NQ = \frac{2 \sqrt{3}}{3} - x \cos 45^\circ.$

Note that $\cos 75^\circ = \frac{\sqrt{6} + \sqrt{2}}{4}$ and $\cos 45^\circ = \frac{\sqrt{2}}{2}.$  Then
\begin{align*}
JP - KQ &= \frac{1}{3} (3 - 2 \sqrt{3}) + x \cos 75^\circ - \left( \frac{2 \sqrt{3}}{3} - x \cos 45^\circ \right) \\
&= \frac{1}{3} (3 - 2 \sqrt{3}) + x \cdot \frac{\sqrt{6} + \sqrt{2}}{4} - \frac{2 \sqrt{3}}{3} + x \cdot \frac{\sqrt{2}}{2} \\
&= \frac{1}{3} - \frac{2 \sqrt{3}}{3} + \frac{x \sqrt{6} + x \sqrt{2}}{4} + \frac{x \sqrt{2}}{2} \\
&= \frac{1}{3} - \frac{2 \sqrt{3}}{3} + \frac{3x \sqrt{2} + x \sqrt{6}}{4}.
\end{align*}

Hence,
\[\tan \angle JMK = \frac{JP - KQ}{x} = \frac{1}{3x} - \frac{2 \sqrt{3}}{3x} + \frac{3 \sqrt{2}}{4} + \frac{\sqrt{6}}{4}.\]Then
\begin{align*}
\angle JMK &= \arctan \left( \frac{1}{3x} - \frac{2 \sqrt{3}}{3x} + \frac{3 \sqrt{2}}{4} + \frac{\sqrt{6}}{4} \right) \\
&= \arctan \left( \frac{1 - 2 \sqrt{3} x}{3x} \right) + \arctan \frac{2 \sqrt{2} + \sqrt{6}}{3}.
\end{align*}We know that $\tan 30^\circ = \frac{1}{\sqrt{3}},$ so $\arctan \frac{1}{\sqrt{3}} = 30^\circ.$  Then
\begin{align*}
\angle JMK &= \arctan \frac{1 - 2 \sqrt{3} x}{3x} + \arctan \frac{2 \sqrt{2} + \sqrt{6}}{3} \\
&= \arctan \frac{1 - 2 \sqrt{3} x}{3x} + \arctan \frac{\sqrt{2}}{2} + \arctan \frac{\sqrt{3}}{3} \\
&= \arctan \frac{1 - 2 \sqrt{3} x}{3x} + 45^\circ + 30^\circ \\
&= \boxed{\arctan \frac{1 - 2 \sqrt{3} x}{3x} + 75^\circ}.
\end{align*}
